With an already poor human rights records, the Theatre CommandingOfficer, Operation Lafiya Dole of the Nigerian Army, Maj. Gen.Olusegun Adeniyi, has told the Nigerian troops to deal without mercywith Boko Haram insurgents and their supporters.The army general stated this yesterday when he visited theheadquarters of Sector 2, Operation Lafiya Dole in  Damaturu, YobeState.Adeniyi said there was no better time than now for the troops to endthe activities of Boko Haram insurgents in the region and country.“Don’t show mercy to Boko Haram insurgents and people supporting theiractivities. All the commanding officers will lead you to deal with thenonsense Boko Haram,” he said.